## Why This Is Asked
Tests the ability to augment a balanced BST to support fast range queries on a multiset with duplicates—a fundamental interview pattern demonstrating understanding of data structure augmentation.

## Key Concepts
- **Treap structure**: Randomized BST with O(log n) expected height
- **Augmented nodes**: cnt tracks duplicates, size maintains subtree element counts
- **Range queries**: countLE(x) finds rank ≤ x; rangeCount derived as countLE(r) - countLE(l-1)
- **Efficient updates**: Size rebalancing occurs only on paths to modified nodes

## Code Example
```python
import random

class TreapNode:
    def __init__(self, key):
        self.key = key
        self.cnt = 1
        self.size = 1
        self.prio = random.random()
        self.left = None
        self.right = None

def update_size(node):
    if node:
        node.size = node.cnt
        if node.left:
            node.size += node.left.size
        if node.right:
            node.size += node.right.size

def rotate_right(p):
    q = p.left
    p.left = q.right
    q.right = p
    update_size(p)
    update_size(q)
    return q

def rotate_left(p):
    q = p.right
    p.right = q.left
    q.left = p
    update_size(p)
    update_size(q)
    return q

def insert(node, key):
    if not node:
        return TreapNode(key)

    if key == node.key:
        node.cnt += 1
    elif key < node.key:
        node.left = insert(node.left, key)
        if node.left.prio < node.prio:
            node = rotate_right(node)
    else:
        node.right = insert(node.right, key)
        if node.right.prio < node.prio:
            node = rotate_left(node)

    update_size(node)
    return node

def count_le(node, x):
    if not node:
        return 0

    if node.key <= x:
        left_size = node.left.size if node.left else 0
        return left_size + node.cnt + count_le(node.right, x)
    else:
        return count_le(node.left, x)

def range_count(node, l, r):
    return count_le(node, r) - count_le(node, l - 1)
```

